quran[16]{c,v,t}:
  19,83,Did you not consider that We send the devils on the infidels to incite them with an incitement
  19,84,"So do not make haste against them, We only number for them, a number (of days)"
  19,85,"The day We will gather those who guard (against evil, like honourable) guests before the Beneficent (Allah)"
  19,86,and We will drive the criminals to hell (like) thirsty (cattle)
  19,87,"none will have the power to mediate except him who has received an agreement, (permission) from the Beneficent (Allah)"
  19,88,"And they say, \"The Beneficent (Allah) has taken (to Him self) a son"
  19,89,You have indeed come with a disastrous thing
  19,90,The skies are about to cleave asunder due to it and the earth to split asunder and the mountains to fall down in pieces
  19,91,that they invoke a son for the Beneficent (Allah)
  19,92,And it does not suit the Beneficent (Allah) that He should take (to Himself) a son
  19,93,there is no one in the skies and the earth but he comes to the Beneficent (Allah) as a servant
  19,94,He has computed them and numbered them a numbering
  19,95,"and everyone of them will come to Him on the day of resurrection, alone"
  19,96,"Those who believe and do righteous works, the Beneficent (Allah) will certainly assign love for them"
  19,97,"So We have made the (Quran) easy in your language only because you should (be able to) convey the good news through it to those who guard (against evil) and warn through it, quarrelsome people"
  19,98,"And how many generations have We destroyed before them, do you find anyone of them or hear (even) their whisper? (R 6, P 15 ½)"